I pay taxes thanks, and a substantial amount of them. <br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;the mortgage business is not driven by the write off<br>
<br>
You mistake me.  The mortgage business isn't *driven* by the mortgage tax reduction.  Certainly all the motivations you mentioned come into play when one decides or doesn't decide to purchase real estate. The mortgage deduction, is, however, indisputably a subsidy both to the mortage industry, and to individual borrowers.  <br>
<br>
And Undine, the problem with repealing the estate tax, or really any federal tax right now, is that there are much larger looming problems with the tax system, specifically:<br>
<br>
1.) Bush's tax cuts combined with his penchant for growing government, and the concomitant funding shortfalls therefrom. Those tax cuts are due to expire, and indeed all current projections by the CBO depend on those tax cuts expiring, for a return to fiscal sanity. If those tax cuts don't expire, we face a very, very grim fiscal picture over the next 25+ years.<br>
<br>
2.) The soon to be massive expansion of the AMT.  No one seriously believes that this will remain as is.  The AMT will affect too many people to remain unchanged.  And unless I miss my guess, many of those affected by the AMT probably also fall into the &quot;regular voter&quot; category.  AMT, however, is the ballast that is keeping the Bush deficit balloon from soaring into the stratosphere.<br>
<br>
3.) Given that Bush will likely try to keep *both* his tax cut, and some kind of fix to the AMT, we're left holding a very empty revenue bag.  Cutting another tax, particularly one that applies to so few in the country, just seems irresponsible, unless there is corresponding talk of some kind of revenue replacement to go with it.  The thinking shown by Bush and those in Congress on this so far is like Nero playing his harp as Rome burns. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p075.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=undinerz>UndineRZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#333333>(4/19/05 11:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3301.topic&index=73>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Estate tax repeal pending in the house--grats Wealthfare</span><hr size=1> Egads....I'm actually responding same day and not a month down the road.  <br>
